wikipedia_page.main: Alfred William Jewett (15 November 1899 – 13 July 1980) was an English footballer who made 38 appearances in the Football League playing for Lincoln City and Wigan Borough as a centre half. He was on the books of Southampton and Arsenal, without representing either club in the league, and also played non-league football for Bitterne United, Thornycrofts, and Bournemouth & Boscombe Athletic.
